Fusion21 is developing a new framework for the supply of materials to Fusion21 Members across the public sector. The objective of this framework is to deliver a best practice material supply offer for Fusion21 Members for the next 4 years. Fusion21 is seeking to engage with the supply market to understand suppliers views on the potential for a new materials offer, ensuring it will be reflective of the best practice capabilities that exist with suppliers in this market. We would encourage you to: (a) complete the survey designed to gain your feedback on the structure and scope of the framework via this link: https://www.surveymonkey.co.uk/r/2XFWQFR; and (b) register your interest in the opportunity by confirming your details and the lots you intend to bid for here: https://fusion21.delta-esourcing.com/respond/44JDE788CH

The authority has identified a requirement for a single supplier framework agreement for linguistic services in support of Permanent Joint Headquarters (PJHQ) and other user worldwide operations. This requirement shall include linguists at a variety of skill and security clearance levels to meet pre-defined roles but will also necessitate short notice deployments in to emerging operational locations when required by the authority. The authority will be looking to place a contract for four (4) years, with the potential to extend for a further twenty-four (24) months. The authority will be looking to place a contract notice for this requirement, with further details of the requirement, in the next 1-4 months. Interested suppliers will be expected to complete a Dynamic Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (DPQQ) with a minimum of three suppliers taken through to the invitation to tender (ITT) stage

a) Der Auftraggeber ist ausschließlich Sektorenauftraggeber nach § 100 Abs. 1 Nr. 2 GWB. b) Hinweise zum Verfahrensablauf: In der 1. Phase der Interessenbekundung haben Unternehmen zunächst nur allgemein ihr Interesse an der Teilnahme am Vergabeverfahren zu bekunden. Der Auftraggeber hat hierfür ein Formblatt erstellt. Das Formblatt kann nach Ziffer I.3 der vorliegenden Bekanntmachung abgerufen werden. Die Interessenbekundungen müssen in Textform über die Vergabeplattform des Auftraggebers bis zum Schlusstermin für deren Eingang nach Ziffer IV.2.2) eingehen. Eine Interessenbekundung als Bewerbergemeinschaft ist möglich. Die Einreichung der Eignungsunterlagen (entsprechend dem Teilnahmeantrag) ist in dieser Phase nicht erforderlich. Ein Unternehmen, das sein Interesse in der 1. Phase nicht bekundet hat, kann im weiteren Verlauf des Vergabeverfahrens nicht berücksichtigt werden. Der Auftraggeber wird in der 2. Phase des Vergabeverfahrens die Unternehmen, die frist- und formgerecht eine Interessenbekundung eingereicht haben, auffordern ihr Interesse zu bestätigen (Interessensbestätigung), in dem die in der entsprechenden Aufforderung aufgeführten Eignungsunterlagen eingereicht werden (Teilnahmeantrag). Eine Bewerbergemeinschaft kann in dieser Phase nur noch mit Unternehmen gebildet werden, die zur Interessenbestätigung aufgefordert wurden. In der Aufforderung zur Interessenbestätigung werden die für die Teilnahme maßgeblichen Informationen mitgeteilt werden. In der 3. Phase werden die erfolgreichen Bewerber zur Angabe eines Angebots aufgefordert. Der Auftraggeber behält sich nach § 15 Abs. 4 SektVO vor, den Auftrag auf der Grundlage der Erstangebote zu vergeben, ohne in Verhandlungen einzutreten. c) Die in Ziffer II.2.7) und in Ziffer IV.2.3) enthaltenen Zeitangaben stehen unter dem Vorbehalt der Anpassung und Aktualisierung. d) Fragen zum Vergabeverfahren sind elektronisch in Textform über die eVergabe-Plattform gem. Ziffer I.3 einzureichen. Fragen sind rechtzeitig gestellt, wenn sie bis spätestens zum 20.3.2020 eingegangen sind. e) Der Auftraggeber behält sich vor, bei Unterschreitung der Mindestzahl von drei zulassungsfähigen Bewerbungen das vorliegende Vergabeverfahren einzustellen. Der Auftraggeber behält sich zudem vor, bei einer Unterschreitung der Mindestzahl von drei wertungsfähigen Angeboten das vorliegende Vergabeverfahren einzustellen. Bei einer losweisen Vergabe gelten die voranstehenden Vorbehalte für jedes Los.

xpaths.value: This call is exclusively addressed to natural persons (and not to legal persons, such as companies), with the specific requirements referred to in Section 5.
the applicant shall have the economic and financial capacity to provide the services set out in this document (see the declaration in point 3 of the Application Form).

Experts shall be selected for the list on the basis of their professional and technical ability to carry out the tasks described in this document. In order to be placed on this list of experts by the European Parliament, the applicant shall:
— have a sound communication, academic or scientific background, with proven experience in science communication; he/she must have at least 4 years' professional experience in science communication, including at least 2 years clearly related to at least 1 of the policy fields in question, alternatively he/she must have a solid professional background linked to at least 1 of the thematic areas listed in paragraph 1.1, with 4 years’ proven professional experience in that area,
— have an excellent command of English (duly proven through publications in English, language certificates, etc.),
Applicants must provide evidence of their ability, skills, experience and competence for performing the work by means of:
— a motivation letter of no more than 2 pages (max. 500 words), in which the applicant sets out his/her reasons for applying and the principal reasons why he/she should be admitted, including the thematic area/s he/she is interested in publishing about,
— a full curriculum vitae, specifying specifies his/her educational and professional background, relevant expertise and experience and knowledge of languages; following the basic structure of the Europass template, the curriculum vitae should be organized as follows: personal information, work experience, education and training, level(s) of (foreign) language competence, personal skills and competences (with scientific/academic relevance), additional information pertinent for this call for expression of interest (e.g. publications, ongoing or planned research projects, awards received, etc.).

xpaths.value: Demande d'informations nº DI 123/DSSFT ayant pour objet le recueil d'informations sur les solutions industrielles dans le domaine des recycleurs de plongée destinés à la guerre des mines
Provision of Worldwide Linguistic Services in Support of UK MoD Operations

Dans le cadre de l'approvisionnement en matériel de plongée pour les armées françaises, le SSF souhaite approfondir sa connaissance de l'offre industrielle en matière de recycleurs destinés à la guerre des mines.
Cette Demande d'informations (DI) vise à identifier et évaluer les solutions possibles, sous les angles techniques et financiers.
Elle ne constitue pas une consultation liée à un marché public, ni un acte d'achat, ni un quelconque engagement de l'administration à lancer ultérieurement une opération sur le même objet. Le dossier de consultation complet incluant modalités de réponse est consultable sur le site https://www.ixarm.com/fr/node/861985 (RFI nº 123).

The scope of this lot includes the supply and, where required, delivery of general building materials and associated services for planned works, new build, investment and repairs and maintenance works. This would include, but not be limited to products including timber, boards, roofing, insulation, brick and block, paving, landscape materials and drainage, cement and plaster, carpentry and woodwork, tool purchase (all hardware), kitchens and bathrooms, alarms (smoke/heat/carbon monoxide); ironmongery and any other general building materials.

The scope of this lot includes the supply and, where required, delivery of electrical products and associated services for planned, new build, responsive repair and compliance works. This would include, but not be limited to; cable and wiring, lighting fixtures and fittings, fire and heat detection alarms, circuit protection, ventilation products, electrical accessories, adherence to WEEE regulations

The scope of this lot provides the opportunity to access the supply and delivery of plumbing and heating products and associated services for; new build, planned and responsive repair works — Including, but not limited to, commercial and domestic heating and plumbing systems and spares, communal heating systems, brassware, showering, consumables and associated accessories, Also access to the supply and delivery of gas heating spares and associated services for domestic boilers and fires.

The scope of this lot provides opportunity to access a bespoke designed supply and service for both planned and reactive works and maintenance. This would include the supply of a broad range of products, including, but not limited to; plumbing and heating products; building materials; electrical items; gas spares; tool purchase; any other associated services and requirements within the scope of the framework (across all lots). The location of the store may be on the Members own premises, a dedicated facility or via a dedicated section of the suppliers trade store.

The scope of this lot includes the provision of local bespoke supply and service requirements for both planned and reactive maintenance through Independent merchants who are Members of an awarded national association or body – to include the supply of a broad range of products, including, but not limited to, plumbing and heating products, building materials, electrical; giving members the opportunity to reinvest their funds in local businesses and independent traders where desired. This can be structured by geographic region or on national basis dependent upon the specific requirement.

The scope of this lot provides the supply and, where required, delivery of all grades of roofing materials & associated services required to increase the lifespan of resident homes for planned, new build and maintenance works as well as non-residential properties. Products should include but are not limited to; slates, felts, sheets, tiles, accessories and fixings – flat and pitched roofs.

Provides the supply and delivery of cabinets, units and associated shelving, doors and drawers of all materials, supplied either flat pack or pre-assembled (rigid), manufactured for primary application in a domestic kitchen environment. Kitchen worktops — fabricated primarily for installation in domestic kitchen applications, of all materials including, but not limited to, stone/granite etc., solid surface (e.g. Corian) etc., wood and laminates. Sinks and associated brassware for use in domestic kitchens, including all materials – stainless steel, ceramic, composite etc., of all sizes, 1 bowl, 1.5 bowl, 2 bowl etc. Pillar taps, mixer taps, combination taps (i.e. with integral shower/water filter etc.) are also included. And associated services required to increase the lifespan of the properties for planned, new build and maintenance works.

The scope of this lot provides for the supply and delivery of all bathrooms and other fixtures and fittings and associated services required for planned, new build and maintenance works. Products should include but are not limited to; sinks, bath and sanitary ware, shower units, cabinets, brassware.

The scope of this lot includes the supply and delivery of: A. of PVC-u (and other plastic composites) windows and doors; B. of Aluminium (and other metals) windows and doors; C. of timber (incl. modified timber) windows and doors; D. of specialist external door sets (fire doors/flood doors). Window suppliers to conduct surveys on behalf of the members if required

The scope of this lot provides for the supply and delivery of adapted bathrooms and other fixtures and fittings and associated services required to increase the lifespan of properties for planned, new build and maintenance works. Products should include but are not limited to, wet rooms, shower trays, adapted showers, brassware, mobility support, general disabled adaptations.

The authority has identified a requirement for a single supplier framework agreement for linguistic services in support of Permanent Joint Headquarters (PJHQ) and other user worldwide operations. This requirement shall include linguists at a variety of skill and security clearance levels to meet pre-defined roles but will also necessitate short notice deployments in to emerging operational locations when required by the authority. The authority will be looking to place a contract for four (4) years, with the potential to extend for a further twenty-four (24) months. The authority will be looking to place a contract notice for this requirement, with further details of the requirement, in the next 1-4 months. Interested suppliers will be expected to complete a Dynamic Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (DPQQ) with a minimum of three suppliers taken through to the invitation to tender (ITT) stage
